      • asSynchronized

        MutableSetIterableMultimap<K,V> asSynchronized()
        Description copied from interface: MutableMultimap
        Returns a synchronized (thread-safe) multimap backed by this multimap. In order to guarantee serial access, it is critical that all access to the backing multimap is accomplished through the returned multimap.

        The returned multimap does not pass the hashCode and equals operations through to the backing multimap, but relies on Object's equals and hashCode methods. This is necessary to preserve the contracts of these operations.

        The returned multimap will be serializable if this multimap is serializable.

        Specified by:
        asSynchronized in interface MutableMultimap<K,V>
        Returns:
        a synchronized view of this multimap.
